article.description: — Orlando Robinson scored 22 points and Jordan Campbell 12 and Fresno State beat Santa Clara 59-52 in the championship game of the SoCal Challenge on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Fresno St. takes down Santa Clara 59-52 for 5-0 start
article.linkText: Fresno St. takes down Santa Clara 59-52 for 5-0 start
article.story: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO, Calif. -- — Orlando Robinson scored 22 points and Jordan Campbell 12 and Fresno State beat Santa Clara 59-52 in the championship game of the SoCal Challenge on Wednesday night. Fresno State is 5-0 to start the season for the first time since the 2015-16 season when the Bulldogs opened with the same record, later won the 2016 Mountain West Conference Tournament and played in the 2016 NCAA Tournament. Isaiah Hill's 3-pointer with 12:51 before halftime gave the Bulldogs (5-0) a 16-13 lead and they led the rest of the way. Fresno State led 27-25 at intermission and steadily created space. Robinson’s layup with 13:36 left gave Fresno State its first double-digit lead of the game at 40-21. Keshawn Justice made back-to-back 3s to bring Santa Clara with 53-49 with 1:22 left but it never got closer. Justice and PJ Pipes each scored 12 for the Broncos (5-1) and Jalen Williams 10. ------
